This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with reinforcement learning and policy gradient algorithms. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics) as these fields often use reinforcement learning for decision-making tasks. Additionally, it may belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it deals with control of a system with a state transition function. Finally, it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it proposes a new algorithm for solving a specific problem.
